Mix cumin, turmeric, allspice, and curry powder together in a small bowl. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-low heat. Cook and stir ginger and cumin mixture in the hot oil until fragrant, about 5 minutes. Stir onion and garlic into the ginger mixture; cook and stir until the onion is hot, 1 to 2 minutes. potatoes; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes. Mix red bell pepper, broccoli, bok choy, and plantains into the the potato mixture. Pour enough water into the skillet to reach about half-full. Cover skillet and cook the mixture at a simmer until the potatoes are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Season with salt.